The paper deals with Generative Adversarial Networks (GANs) for image synthesis, which is a popular topic in computer vision (CV) research. Therefore, cs.CV is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a new architecture for GANs, which involves deep fully connected layers and pooling layers, indicating that it may be relevant to machine learning (LG), artificial intelligence (AI), and neural networks (NE) research. Finally, the paper involves the use of convolutional networks, which may also make it relevant to graphics (GR) research.
